# Mindbody Analytics API Reference

## Overview
The Mindbody Analytics API provides intro offer tracking and student data for Yoga Health Center.
It is hosted at: `https://mind-body-analytics-remix.replit.app`
Authentication: Bearer token via `MINDBODY_API_KEY` environment variable.

## Base Configuration
- Base URL: `https://mind-body-analytics-remix.replit.app`
- Auth Header: `Authorization: Bearer <MINDBODY_API_KEY>`
- Content-Type: `application/json`

## Endpoints

### GET /api/v1/intro-offers
Returns paginated list of intro offer records.

**Query Parameters:**
| Parameter | Type   | Description                          |
|-----------|--------|--------------------------------------|
| status    | string | Filter by member status              |
| since     | string | Filter by date (ISO 8601)            |
| limit     | number | Max records to return (default varies)|
| offset    | number | Pagination offset                    |

**Response Shape:**
```json
{
  "data": [IntroOffer],
  "meta": {
    "count": number,
    "limit": number,
    "offset": number
  }
}
```

**IntroOffer Object:**
| Field                        | Type    | Description                                      |
|------------------------------|---------|--------------------------------------------------|
| id                           | string  | Unique offer ID                                  |
| studentId                    | string  | Associated student ID                            |
| firstName                    | string  | Student first name                               |
| lastName                     | string  | Student last name                                |
| email                        | string? | Student email                                    |
| phone                        | string? | Student phone number                             |
| offerName                    | string  | Name of the intro offer purchased                |
| offerCategory                | string  | Category (e.g., "IntroOffer")                    |
| purchaseAmount               | string  | Dollar amount paid (e.g., "75.00")               |
| purchaseDate                 | string  | ISO 8601 datetime of purchase                    |
| classesAttendedSincePurchase | number  | Number of classes attended since purchase         |
| lastAttendanceDate           | string? | ISO 8601 datetime of last class attended (null if never) |
| daysSinceLastAttendance      | number? | Days since last class (null if never attended)    |
| daysSincePurchase            | number  | Days elapsed since purchase                      |
| hasConverted                 | boolean | Whether student converted to full membership     |
| conversionDate               | string? | ISO 8601 datetime of conversion (null if not)    |
| conversionType               | string? | Type of conversion (null if not converted)       |
| conversionAmount             | string? | Dollar amount of conversion purchase (null if not)|
| memberStatus                 | string  | Current status (see values below)                |
| expirationDate               | string? | Intro offer expiration date (null if not set)    |

**Member Status Values (maps to "Stage" in UI):**
- `new` - Purchased but hasn't attended any classes yet (shown as "purchased" badge)
- `engaged` - Actively attending classes (shown as "engaged" badge)
- `at_risk` - Attendance has dropped off, needs follow-up (shown as "at risk" badge)
- `lapsed` - No recent attendance, likely lost (shown as "lapsed" badge)
- `converted` - Converted to a full membership (shown as "converted" badge)

### PATCH /api/v1/intro-offers/:id
Update an intro offer record.

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "status": "string (optional)",
  "notes": "string (optional)"
}
```

**Response:** Updated IntroOffer object.

## Proposed Communication Endpoints (For mbanalytics to implement)

These endpoints need to be added to mbanalytics to enable two-way communication sync with YHC Way.

### GET /api/v1/intro-offers/:id/communications
Returns list of communications for an intro offer.

**Query Parameters:**
| Parameter | Type   | Description                          |
|-----------|--------|--------------------------------------|
| since     | string | Filter by date (ISO 8601)            |
| limit     | number | Max records to return (default 50)   |
| offset    | number | Pagination offset                    |
| channel   | string | Filter by channel (email, sms)       |

**Response Shape:**
```json
{
  "data": [Communication],
  "meta": {
    "count": number,
    "limit": number,
    "offset": number
  }
}
```

**Communication Object:**
| Field            | Type    | Description                                    |
|------------------|---------|------------------------------------------------|
| id               | string  | Unique communication ID                        |
| offerId          | string  | Associated intro offer ID                      |
| studentId        | string  | Associated student ID                          |
| channel          | string  | "email" or "sms"                               |
| direction        | string  | "outbound" or "inbound"                        |
| subject          | string? | Email subject line (null for SMS)              |
| body             | string? | Message body/content                           |
| recipientAddress | string? | Email address or phone number                  |
| status           | string? | "sent", "delivered", "initiated", "failed"     |
| sentAt           | string  | ISO 8601 datetime when sent                    |
| createdBy        | string? | Name of user who sent it                       |
| idempotencyKey   | string? | Used for deduplication (format: "yhcway-{id}") |

### POST /api/v1/intro-offers/:id/communications
Create a communication record. Used by YHC Way to push outbound communications.

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "channel": "email" | "sms",
  "direction": "outbound" | "inbound",
  "subject": "string (optional)",
  "body": "string (optional)",
  "recipientAddress": "string (optional)",
  "status": "sent" | "delivered" | "initiated",
  "sentAt": "ISO 8601 datetime",
  "createdBy": "string (optional)",
  "idempotencyKey": "string (required for dedup)"
}
```

**Deduplication Rules:**
- If `idempotencyKey` matches an existing record, return the existing record (200) without creating a duplicate
- Format convention: `yhcway-{local_id}` for records originating from YHC Way
- Format convention: `mb-{remote_id}` for records originating from mbanalytics

**Response:** `{ "data": Communication }` (the created or existing record)

### Sync Strategy
1. **Pull**: YHC Way calls GET to fetch remote communications, deduplicates by `externalId + source`, and inserts new records locally
2. **Push**: When email/SMS is sent from YHC Way, it logs locally first, then POSTs to mbanalytics with `idempotencyKey = "yhcway-{localId}"`
3. **Source of Truth**: mbanalytics is authoritative. On conflict, mbanalytics data wins
4. **Sync Trigger**: Manual "Sync" button per student, or automatic on student detail modal open

## Integration in The YHC Way

### Server Layer
- File: `server/mindbodyAnalytics.ts` - API client functions (proxies to external API)
- File: `server/routes.ts` - Express routes that proxy to the API + local reminder CRUD

### Server Routes (Proxied to Mindbody Analytics API)
| Route                                  | Method | Description                |
|----------------------------------------|--------|----------------------------|
| /api/mindbody-analytics/status         | GET    | Check if API is configured |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers   | GET    | Get intro offers (proxied) |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:id | PATCH | Update an intro offer      |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/students       | GET    | Get students (proxied)     |

### Server Routes (Local - Reminders stored in PostgreSQL)
| Route                                                    | Method | Description              |
|----------------------------------------------------------|--------|--------------------------|
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:id/reminders       | GET    | Get reminders for offer  |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:id/reminders       | POST   | Create a reminder        |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:offerId/reminders/:reminderId | PATCH | Toggle reminder completed |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:offerId/reminders/:reminderId | DELETE | Delete a reminder        |

### Server Routes (Local - Communications with two-way sync)
| Route                                                           | Method | Description                    |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------|--------|--------------------------------|
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:id/communications         | GET    | Get communications for offer   |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:id/communications         | POST   | Create communication + push to mbanalytics |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:offerId/communications/:commId | DELETE | Delete a communication    |
| /api/mindbody-analytics/intro-offers/:id/communications/sync    | POST   | Pull from mbanalytics + push unsynced |

**Communication Object (local DB - `intro_offer_communications` table):**
| Field            | Type      | Description                              |
|------------------|-----------|------------------------------------------|
| id               | serial    | Auto-increment primary key               |
| tenantId         | integer?  | Tenant isolation                         |
| offerId          | text      | Links to intro offer ID                  |
| studentId        | text      | Links to student ID                      |
| channel          | text      | "email" or "sms"                         |
| direction        | text      | "outbound" or "inbound"                  |
| subject          | text?     | Email subject line                       |
| body             | text?     | Message body/content                     |
| recipientAddress | text?     | Email address or phone number            |
| status           | text?     | "sent", "delivered", "initiated"         |
| sentAt           | timestamp | When the communication was sent          |
| createdBy        | text?     | Name of user who created it              |
| source           | text      | "yhcway" or "mbanalytics"                |
| externalId       | text?     | ID from mbanalytics for synced records   |
| syncStatus       | text?     | "pending" or "synced"                    |
| syncedAt         | timestamp?| When last synced with mbanalytics        |
| metadata         | jsonb?    | Additional data                          |
| createdAt        | timestamp | When record was created                  |

**Auto-logging Behavior:**
- Email: When an email is sent via Gmail compose, a communication record is auto-created with channel="email", direction="outbound"
- SMS: When SMS is initiated via Google Voice link, a communication record is auto-created with channel="sms", direction="outbound", status="initiated"
- Both are automatically pushed to mbanalytics (when the API endpoints exist) with idempotency keys

**Reminder Object (local DB - `intro_offer_reminders` table):**
| Field       | Type    | Description                    |
|-------------|---------|--------------------------------|
| id          | serial  | Auto-increment primary key     |
| offerId     | text    | Links to intro offer ID        |
| tenantId    | integer?| Tenant isolation               |
| title       | text    | Reminder title                 |
| description | text?   | Optional description           |
| completed   | boolean | Whether reminder is done       |
| createdBy   | text?   | Name of user who created it    |
| createdAt   | timestamp | When reminder was created    |

### Frontend Pages
- `client/src/pages/intro-offers.tsx` - **Intro Offer Funnel** page
  - Table view matching mbanalytics layout: Name, Offer, Amount, Purchase, Expires, Classes, Last Class, Stage, Conversion, Actions
  - Actions column: Email (Gmail compose) and SMS (Google Voice) buttons
  - Clicking a row opens a student detail modal
  - Student modal includes: stat cards, offer info, contact info, and tabs for Communications/Reminders/Classes/Purchases/Notes
  - Communications tab: Timeline view of all email/SMS interactions with sync button, source badges, and quick compose actions
- `client/src/pages/scoreboard.tsx` - **Business Scoreboard** (aggregated metrics dashboard)

### Scoreboard Metric Logic
The Business Scoreboard separates metrics into two categories:

**Current Status Metrics (not date-filtered, show all-time current state):**
- Active Members = engaged + new status count
- At Risk = at_risk status count
- Lapsed = lapsed status count
- Converted = hasConverted === true count
- Conversion Rate = converted / total offers
- Awaiting First Class = new status count

**Period-Specific Metrics (filtered by selected date range):**
- New [Period] = offers purchased within selected date range
- Intro Offers Sold = same as New [Period]
- Net Adds = new in period - lapsed in period

**Date Range Options:** Last Week, Last Month, Last 90 Days, Year to Date, Custom Range
